snippet.textDisplay:
One option you could do to keep water sanitary is to use a UV disinfectant lamp on the contaminated water supply. Even turning it on for a few minutes a day would help keep the water clean. Just make sure it doesn't shine on the ants as it would affect them too, especially eggs and larva.

Although, if you left the uncontaminated tube uncovered with a bright light, it would encourage the ants to move out faster.
